  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Mitigating the Negative Effects of the Covid-19 Pandemic</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Community awareness raising working with community-based faith leaders (Community engagement and radio) and face masks 20 communities
2. Train faith and community leaders on Covid-19 prevention and control, focusing on their roles and responsibilities from across 20 communities

3. Cash transfer to vulnerable groups (30 GBP to 100 People)

4. 80 washing kits and 240 soap bars for 20 communities

5. Posters for faith leaders to use in their sensitization with their communities - printing</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">However, Sierra Leone has registered 2,159 cases with 72 death reported and 1,650 recoveries. 
In that regard, CIFD intend to scale up social mobilization activities in 20 communities in the district to prevent further spread of the disease.</narrative>
  </description>
